history.text: Jaws was a great thriller film by Steven Spielberg.
Yes! It has a very high rotten tomatoes rating, and the average rating is excellent too. What do you think about the cast?
They say it is "a sensationally effective action picture." And I agree. It is very good.
The cast was good. I liked Roy Schneider as Chief Martin Brody.
It is definitely an effective action picture. I like that it is both scary and dramatic.
Lorraine Gary was decent as Ellen Brody.
They were correct when they said it is a "scare machine".
I think Richard Dreyfuss was great too. What about Spielberg? The critical responses show what a great director he is.
Yes he is very good. I am glad he made this wonderful thriller film.
It got a 97% on Rotten Tomatoes which is a score I agree with.
I did not know the town was fictional, but I could tell it was obviously set in New England.
Yes Amity Island sounds like a real place.
I like New England and they captured it well.
I thought they did too! I also appreciate that it is adapted from a Peter Benchley novel.
They said it has more zest than a Woody Allen picture. That is a good way to put it.
I liked the beach party scene in the beginning.
Remember when they closed the beaches? That was a good choice.
Me too! That is one of the best scenes for sure. I also like the part where Quint shows up!
I can't believe Quint offered his services for $10000. That was a lot of money back then.
Yes! Of course, the mayor did not want them to close the beaches...
Good thing oceanographer Matt Hooper was there to confirm the death was a shark attack.
That was deifnitely a lot for back then. Yes, Hooper was like the expert?!
Yeah. Remember when the local fisherman tried to catch a large tiger shark?
I can't believe they declared the beach safe. Even after Hooper disputed that.
So, they thought a tiger shark did that?
I guess so.
Then Hooper got that big great white shark's tooth.
I guess when they found the sharks tooth they knew it was a different shark.
Yes that is very true good point.
Oh! I forgot about Brody's son on the boat!
Yeah. Then they got on Orca to hunt the shark.
The scene where the shark attacks the boat is awesome!
Quint tried to hook the shark.
Yeah finally they shoot the tank and kill the shark. Good thing they did that.
Yes! Quint dies- the shark eats him
Too bad for him. Unlike him I am still alive.
At least Hooper and Brody survived.
I did not mean that yes! like that lol- sad when he dies!!
I love the part where they swim back
